ght:bold">Fully upheld</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top"><p style="margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">5</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top"><p style="margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">30</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top"><p style="margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">35</span></p></td></tr></table><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.2pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">Less than 2% of all complaints were actually investigated</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 52.2pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">Less than </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">1</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">% of complaints </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">against PCTs or SHAs </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">were upheld.</span></li></ul><ol start="67" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 39.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">PHSO asserts that "</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Our role is to investigate complaints</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">", and "</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">We work to put things right</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">", but its own figures show that PHSO is failing to investigate complaints and is doing virtually nothing to put things right.</span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 39.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">The chance of any single ticket winning a prize in the UK National lottery is 1.85%. The chance of getting a complaint investigated by the PHSO is 1.61%</span></li></ol><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:1.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:1.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:1.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:1.5pt; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">The chances of the Ombudsman actually investigating any individual complaint are </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">rather less than </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">the chance of winning a prize in the National lottery with a single ticket.</span></p><ol start="69" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 39.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">While the odds are so heavily stacked against complainants, </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">believe </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">that the Ombudsman's office</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt"> is counterproductive: it cultivates</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt"> the illusion of being an independent arbiter, but </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">in reality serves only to give tacit approval to </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">malpractice. </span></li><li style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-weight:normal; margin:12pt 0pt 0pt 39.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt">In both cases, my contact with PHSO staff was minimal: I would have welcomed the opportunity of a meeting, to explain the issues and highlight the key pieces of evidence.  I am sure it would have made their jobs easier, enabled them to resolve any queries quickly and accurately, and significantly increased the chances of a satisfactory outcome. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">PHSO staff appear to have far more empathy with the civil servants they are supposed to be investigating than with the members of the public they are supposed to be protecting.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> The chance of a single ticket winning a prize in the UK National lottery is 1.85%. The chance of getting a complaint investigated by the PHSO is 1.61%   </span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> eg: </span><a href="http://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/news/4434191.Mallon_s_drive_to_expose_DVLA__con_/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/news/4434191.Mallon_s_drive_to_expose_DVLA__con_/</span></a></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">eg: </span><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/watchdog/2011/09/sorn.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/watchdog/2011/09/sorn.html</span></a></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.dvla.gov.uk/media/pdf/publications/business_plan_2008_2009.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.dvla.gov.uk/media/pdf/publications/business_plan_2008_2009.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> (page 15 Target 2)</span></p><p style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/pgr/statistics/datatablespublications/vehicles/excisedutyevasion/ved2008"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:un